description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a dynamic and committed individual to come and work as part of the Lambeth Borough Medicines Optimisation and Long Term Conditions Commissioning Team. The post holder will gain valuable experience in supporting the medicines optimisation agenda across South East London and within the borough of Lambeth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves working on SEL based and Lambeth specific projects and initiatives as required and includes supporting the smooth operation of the SEL Integrated Medicines Optimisation Committee (SEL IMOC, formerly the Area Prescribing Committee) at an exciting time in the NHS. In summary the post holder will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing a comprehensive administrative and business support service to the SEL IMOC and the Lambeth borough based Medicines and Long Term Conditions Commissioning team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the smooth operation of the SEL IMOC and its main sub-group, the Medicines and Pathways Review Group and relevant Lambeth borough led Groups. This includes overall administration of the Committees, agenda planning, meeting coordination and minute taking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining and developing the Medicines Optimisation section of the internet/intranet, ensuring documentation is updated and current.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provision of a standard range of administrative and support functions such as diary management, arranging meetings, handling incoming emails, telephone calls and correspondence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will also undertake small projects working with colleagues in the organisation and external partners/stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Please see the job description and personal specification for full details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please apply early as the vacancy may close before the given closing date when sufficient applications are received.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal queries and information please contact Devika Sennik, (Lead Pharmacist for the SEL IMOC) via: nelcsu.resource@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organisational Context&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lambeth Borough is part of the South East London CCG and is made up of all GP surgeries in the borough. With a budget of approximately £400 million our job is to make the most effective use of this money best meet the health needs of people in Lambeth. Our main providers are Kings College Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, Guys and St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust and South London and the Maudsley NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our strategic ambition is set out in the NHS Long Term Plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly organisation with a thriving health and well-being culture for our staff. We are co-located with Lambeth Council in modern offices in Brixton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The South East London Integrated Medicines Optimisation Committee (SEL IMOC, formerly the Area Prescribing Committee) is a collaboration of all NHS organisations in SEL and has been established since 2013. Lambeth borough hosts the SEL IMOC on behalf of the six SEL boroughs, NHS Acute Trusts and Mental Health Trusts in SEL. The post holder will support the running of the SEL IMOC and will also work as part of the Lambeth borough Medicines and Long Term Conditions Commissioning Team to support implementation of high quality, safe, cost-effective and value based prescribing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘No agencies please’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
